The paper presents a conditional generative model that maps low-dimensional embeddings of multiple modalities of data to a common latent space, which is a problem commonly addressed in machine learning and deep learning research. The paper also discusses the use of a proxy variable trick, which is a technique used in deep learning research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with the extraction of semantic relationships between different modalities of data, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and MultiMedia (cs.MM).
